{{Wikipedia technical help|collapsed}}

{{Wikipedia how to|shortcut1=H:FT}}

This page aims to assist Wikipedians working with biographical articles containing [[:en:Family tree|Family tree]]s.

The most common way is to display a family tree on Wikipedia is as an [[:en:Ahnentafel|Ahnentafel]] by [[Template: Ahnentafel]]. However, there are other options. 

This page originated in examples taken from a discussion on the [[Wikipedia:Village pump|Village pump]] in March/April 2005 (see [[Wikipedia talk:Family trees|Talk page]]). It has since been updated to use later created templates.

== Ahnentafel ==
{{Main|Template:Ahnentafel}}
The simplest way to include a list of ancestors is the [[:en:Ahnentafel|Ahnentafel]]. This is a standard for genealogists, but it is hard to understand for people who have not seen it before.

# [[William, Prince of Wales]] (born 21 June 1982)
# [[:en:Charles III|Charles III]] (born 14 November 1948)
# [[:en:Diana, Princess of Wales|Diana, Princess of Wales]] née Lady Diana Spencer (1 July 1961 – 31 August 1997)
# [[Prince Philip, Duke of Edinburgh]] (10 June 1921 – 9 April 2021)
# [[:en:Elizabeth II|Elizabeth II]] (21 April 1926 – 8 September 2022)
# [[John Spencer, 8th Earl Spencer]] (24 January 1924 – 29 March 1992)
# [[:en:Frances Shand Kydd|The Hon Mrs Shand Kydd]] née The Hon Frances Roche (20 January 1936 – 3 June 2004)
#  ...

Ahnentafels can be displayed as horizontal trees using [[Template:Ahnentafel]]:

<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">
{{ahnentafel
|collapsed=yes |align=center
|title=Ancestry of William, Prince of Wales
|boxstyle_1=background-color: #fcc;
|boxstyle_2=background-color: #fb9;
|boxstyle_3=background-color: #ffc;
|boxstyle_4=background-color: #bfc;
|1. '''[[William, Prince of Wales]]'''
|2. [[:en:Charles III|Charles III of the United Kingdom]]
|3. [[:en:Diana, Princess of Wales|Lady Diana Spencer]]
|4. [[Prince Philip, Duke of Edinburgh|Prince Philip of Greece and Denmark]]
|5. [[:en:Elizabeth II|Elizabeth II of the United Kingdom]]
|6. [[John Spencer, 8th Earl Spencer]]
|7. [[:en:Frances Shand Kydd|The Honourable Frances Roche]]
|8. [[Prince Andrew of Greece and Denmark]]
|9. [[Princess Alice of Battenberg]]
|10. [[:en:George VI|George VI of the United Kingdom]]
|11. [[Queen Elizabeth The Queen Mother|Lady Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon]]
|12. [[:en:Albert Spencer, 7th Earl Spencer|Albert Spencer, 7th Earl Spencer]]
|13. [[:en:Cynthia Spencer, Countess Spencer|Lady Cynthia Hamilton]]
|14. [[Maurice Roche, 4th Baron Fermoy]]
|15. [[Ruth Roche, Baroness Fermoy|Ruth Gill]]
}}</syntaxhighlight>

{{ahnentafel
|collapsed=no |align=center
|title=Ancestry of William, Prince of Wales
|boxstyle_1=background-color: #fcc;
|boxstyle_2=background-color: #fb9;
|boxstyle_3=background-color: #ffc;
|boxstyle_4=background-color: #bfc;
|1. '''[[William, Prince of Wales]]'''
|2. [[:en:Charles III|Charles III of the United Kingdom]]
|3. [[:en:Diana, Princess of Wales|Lady Diana Spencer]]
|4. [[Prince Philip, Duke of Edinburgh|Prince Philip of Greece and Denmark]]
|5. [[:en:Elizabeth II|Elizabeth II of the United Kingdom]]
|6. [[John Spencer, 8th Earl Spencer]]
|7. [[:en:Frances Shand Kydd|The Honourable Frances Roche]]
|8. [[Prince Andrew of Greece and Denmark]]
|9. [[Princess Alice of Battenberg]]
|10. [[:en:George VI|George VI of the United Kingdom]]
|11. [[Queen Elizabeth The Queen Mother|Lady Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon]]
|12. [[:en:Albert Spencer, 7th Earl Spencer|Albert Spencer, 7th Earl Spencer]]
|13. [[:en:Cynthia Spencer, Countess Spencer|Lady Cynthia Hamilton]]
|14. [[Maurice Roche, 4th Baron Fermoy]]
|15. [[Ruth Roche, Baroness Fermoy|Ruth Gill]]
}}

Ancestry trees are usually displayed collapsed; to display them expanded add the parameter: <code>|collapsed=no</code> to {{tlx|ahnentafel}}

== Tree chart template ==
{{Main|Template:Tree chart}}
[[Template:Tree chart]] can be used to construct simple (or incredibly complex: see [[Japanese imperial family tree]]) using an ASCII art-like syntax:

<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">
{{Chart top|My family tree}}
{{Tree chart/start|align=center}}
{{Tree chart| | | | GRM |~|y|~| GRP | | GRM=Grandma|GRP=Grandpa}}
{{Tree chart| | | | | | | |)|-|-|-|.| }}
{{Tree chart| | | MUM |y| DAD | |DAISY| MUM=Mum|DAD=Dad|DAISY=Aunt Daisy}}
{{Tree chart| |,|-|-|-|+|-|-|-|.| | | }}
{{Tree chart| JOE | | ME | | SIS | | | JOE=My brother Joe|ME='''Me!'''|SIS=My little sister
       |boxstyle_ ME=background-color: #bfc;}}
{{Tree chart/end}}
{{chart bottom}}
</syntaxhighlight>

{{Chart top|My family tree|collapsed=no}}
{{Tree chart/start|align=center}}
{{Tree chart| | | | GRM |~|y|~| GRP | | GRM=Grandma|GRP=Grandpa}}
{{Tree chart| | | | | | | |)|-|-|-|.| }}
{{Tree chart| | | MUM |y| DAD | |DAISY| MUM=Mum|DAD=Dad|DAISY=Aunt Daisy}}
{{Tree chart| |,|-|-|-|+|-|-|-|.| | | }}
{{Tree chart| JOE | | ME | | SIS | | | JOE=My brother Joe|ME='''Me!'''|SIS=My little sister 
       |boxstyle_ ME=background-color: #bfc;}}
{{Tree chart/end}}
{{Chart bottom}}

{{tlx|Tree chart}} can also be used to create a Continental European style bottom to top layout for an [[:en:Ahnentafel|Ahnentafel]] tree, or just as easily a top down (not shown)
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">
{{Chart top|width=100%|European style family tree bottom to top (William, Prince of Wales)}}
{{Tree chart/start|align=center}}
{{Tree chart| |boxstyle=background-color: #bfc|Ah8|v|Ah9| |Ah10|v|Ah11| | |  |Ah12|v|Ah13| | |Ah14|v|Ah15|
  |Ah8=8. [[Prince Andrew of Greece and Denmark]] |Ah9=9. [[Princess Alice of Battenberg]]
  |Ah10=10. [[:en:George VI|George VI of the United Kingdom]] |Ah11=11. [[Queen Elizabeth The Queen Mother|Lady Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon]]
  |Ah12=12. [[:en:Albert Spencer, 7th Earl Spencer|Albert Spencer, 7th Earl Spencer]]  |Ah13=13. [[:en:Cynthia Spencer, Countess Spencer|Lady Cynthia Hamilton]]
  |Ah14=14. [[Maurice Roche, 4th Baron Fermoy]]  |Ah15=15. [[Ruth Roche, Baroness Fermoy|Ruth Gill]]}}
| | | | |!| | | | | | | |!| | | | | | | | | |!| | | | | | | | |!}}
{{Tree chart|boxstyle=background-color: #ffc;| | | |Ah4|-|-|v|-|-|Ah5| | | | | |  | |Ah6|-|-|-|v|-|-|Ah7 
  |Ah4=4. [[Prince Philip, Duke of Edinburgh|Prince Philip of Greece and Denmark]] |Ah5=5. [[:en:Elizabeth II|Elizabeth II of the United Kingdom]] 
  |Ah6=6. [[John Spencer, 8th Earl Spencer]]  |Ah7=7. [[:en:Frances Shand Kydd|The Honourable Frances Roche]]
  }}
{{Tree chart| | | | | | | | |!| | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |!}}
{{Tree chart|boxstyle=background-color: #fb9;| | | | | | | |Ah2|-|-|-|-|-|-|-|v|-|-|-|-|-|-|-|-|Ah3
  |Ah2=2. [[:en:Charles III|Charles III of the United Kingdom]]|Ah3=3. [[:en:Diana, Princess of Wales|Lady Diana Spencer]]}}
{{Tree chart| | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |!}}
{{Tree chart|boxstyle=background-color: #fcc;| | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |Ah1  |Ah1=1.'''[[William, Prince of Wales]]'''}}
{{Tree chart/end}}
{{Chart bottom}}  
</syntaxhighlight>

Note: any letter number combination that is not reserved as a tile descriptor in {{tlx|Tree chart}} can be used. In this example Ah1...Ah15 is short for Ahnentafel1...Ahnentafel15


{{Chart top|width=100%|European style family tree bottom to top (William, Prince of Wales)|collapsed=no}}
